SIMPLE: entangle
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Entangle
<hw>En*tan"gle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Entangled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Entangling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To twist or interweave in such a manner as not to be easily
separated; to make tangled, confused, and intricate; <as>as, to
<ex>entangle</ex> yarn or the hair</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To involve in such complications as to render
extrication a bewildering difficulty; hence, metaphorically, to insnare;
to perplex; to bewilder; to puzzle; <as>as, to <ex>entangle</ex> the
feet in a net, or in briers</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Entangling</xex>
alliances.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Washington.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The difficulties that perplex men's thoughts and
<qex>entangle</qex> their understandings.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Allowing her to <qex>entangle</qex> herself with a person whose
future was so uncertain.</q> <rj><qau>Froude.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>entangled</ent>⟦br⟧
